    slug: "tajweed-juz-ammah-30th-part",
    description: `Tajweed Juz Ammah (30th Part) is a specialized edition of the thirtieth and final portion of the Holy Quran, published with comprehensive tajweed (Quranic recitation science) color-coding and markings to assist readers in applying the rules of proper Quranic pronunciation. Juz Ammah, which contains Surah an-Naba through Surah an-Nas (thirty-seven surahs in total), is the portion of the Quran that most Muslims first learn to recite and memorize, making it the ideal starting point for anyone studying the science of tajweed. This edition uses a carefully designed color-coding system where different tajweed rules — such as the elongation (madd), nasalization (ghunnah), heaviness (tafkheem), lightness (tarqeeq), and the various types of stopping (waqf) — are each marked with a distinct color, allowing the reader to identify and apply the correct pronunciation for every letter and word.

The science of tajweed is based on a set of precise rules governing how each letter of the Arabic alphabet should be articulated from its specific point of origin (makhraj) within the mouth and throat, and the various characteristics (sifaat) that distinguish each letter from others. These rules were established by the early Quran scholars to preserve the exact manner in which the Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) recited the Quran, as conveyed through the chain of authorized reciters extending back to him. Mastery of tajweed is considered obligatory for anyone who recites the Quran, as even small errors in pronunciation can change the meaning of the words. This color-coded edition makes the learning process significantly more accessible by providing visual cues that guide the reader through the application of each rule without requiring them to constantly reference a separate tajweed textbook.

The book includes a detailed introductory section that explains the color-coding system and provides a concise overview of the major tajweed rules with examples from the Quranic text. The Arabic script is printed in a clear, well-spaced format that makes it easy to distinguish individual letters and diacritical marks. The vowelization (tashkeel) is complete and accurate, which is essential for correct recitation. This edition is widely used in Quran schools, madrasahs, and by individual learners who are studying tajweed under the guidance of a qualified teacher or through self-study. The compact size of the Juz Ammah format makes it convenient to carry and use during daily recitation practice. Tajweed Juz Ammah (30th Part) is an excellent tool for both beginners who are just starting to learn the rules of Quranic recitation and more advanced students who want to refine and perfect their application of tajweed in their daily reading of the Quran.`,
